  "doc_id": "20579",
  "text": "The primary endpoint of the study was the percentage change from baseline to week 26 in VAT. Eligibility criteria included the receipt of stable antiretroviral therapy (ART) for at least 8 weeks and presence of abdominal fat accumulation, defined as a waist circumference at least 95 cm and waist-to-hip ratio at least 0.94 for men and a waist circumference at least 94 cm and waist-to-hip ratio at least 0.88 for women (for complete eligibility criteria, see Falutz et al. [CITATION_1] ). Waist circumference and waist-to-hip ratio criteria were based on cutoffs that define increased visceral adiposity (VAT > 130 cm 2 ) in men and women in the general population [CITATION_2] . The study was approved by the Institutional Review Board at each site, and participants provided written informed consent.",
